            "title": "How I made this site",
            "summary": "Today I'm going to tell you how I quickly made this website&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<p class=\"msg msg--highlight \">Today I'm going to tell you how I quickly made this website using <a href=\"https://getpublii.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" title=\"Publii, a new Static CMS with GUI to build an extremely safe, fast and stylish HTML website.\">Publii</a> and hosted it for free on <a href=\"https://pages.github.com/\" title=\"Websites for you and your projects, hosted directly from your GitHub repository. Just edit, push, and your changes are live.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">GitHub Pages</a>.</p>\n<p>My goal was to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">quickly</span> develop and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">host</span> a simple, yet good-looking portfolio\\blog site <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">for free</span>. After some research I found <a href=\"https://getpublii.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" title=\"Publii, a new Static CMS with GUI to build an extremely safe, fast and stylish HTML website.\">Publii</a> - a no-database CMS, that allows to easily upload to <a href=\"https://pages.github.com/\" title=\"Websites for you and your projects, hosted directly from your GitHub repository. Just edit, push, and your changes are live.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">GitHub Pages</a> for a free hosting. And it features a nice set of <a href=\"https://marketplace.getpublii.com/products/category/freebies/\" title=\"Free Publii themes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">free themes</a>!</p>\n<p>Publii is a free desktop app that allows you to edit and manage your site's content using intuitive user interface. No html\\css knowledge required.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://getpublii.com/assets/svg/publii-app.svg\" alt=\"Publii screenshot\" width=\"500\" height=\"289\"></p>\n<p>(Although, I do know how build sites from scratch, I think using a ready solution is smarter than hand-crafting your site from scratch.)</p>\n<p>That's it. I could go more in-depth about setting it up, but there are already <a href=\"https://getpublii.com/docs/host-static-website-github-pages.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" title=\"How to create a static website using Github Pages\">plenty of guides on it</a>.</p>",
